Frank Austin ARCHER, Plaintiff—Appellant, v. Wilbur F. AMONETTE, Doctor; Timothy Paul Thompson; Rebecca Arney, Nurse; Deborah Michelle Kesling, Nurse, Defendants—Appellees. No. 07-6681. United States Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. Submitted: Oct. 11, 2007. Decided: Oct. 17, 2007. Frank Austin Archer, Appellant Pro Se. Before MICHAEL and SHEDD, Circuit Judges, and HAMILTON, Senior Circuit Judge.

*178Affirmed by unpublished PER CURIAM opinion.

Unpublished opinions are not binding precedent in this circuit.

PER CURIAM:

Frank Austin Archer appeals the district court’s order denying relief on his 42 U.S.C. § 1983 (2000) complaint. We have reviewed the record and find no reversible error. Accordingly, we affirm for the reasons stated by the district court. Archer v. Amonette, No. 7:07-cv-00088-GEC, 2007 WL 1094408 (W.D. Va. filed on Apr. 9, 2007 & entered on Apr. 10, 2007). We dispense with oral argument because the facts and legal contentions are adequately presented in the materials before the court and argument would not aid the decisional process.

AFFIRMED.
